fields.description:
EI: 0.5 MD for INT,ACC, PROD

QA: 0,25 MD for INT,ACC, PROD

¬†

Mapping for new customer specific *field "Initial delivery date"* is needed.¬†

For GB delivery import (IDOC) customer sends the information about delivery date. This information is being send in <E1EDT13> segment in field <NTANF>
Example:¬†
<E1EDT13>
<QUALF>003</QUALF>
<NTANF>20250318</NTANF>
<NTANZ>000000</NTANZ>
</E1EDT13>

Now this information is being saved in unloading date - should stay as it is, but also this date needs to be saved in new parameter "initialDeliveryDate".

This field "Initial delivery date"(parameter "initialDeliveryDate") should not be updated, it means:¬†
- With the first import the value of <NTANF>is being mapped to field "Initial delivery date" and to the standard field "Unloading date"
- If the field ‚Äú Initial delivery date‚Äù is already field in, we should not update it when transport is being modified.¬†

¬†

¬†

Example of import is attached. [^GBFOODS.xml]
